sues of fundamental political importance, from war and peace, poverty and wealth, the relation between the sexes, demagoguery and democracy to the role of philosophy and poetry in political society. Accessible to students as well as scholars, The Political Theory of Aristophanes can be utilized easily in the classroom, but at the same time serve as a valuable source for those conducting more advanced research. Whether the field is political philosophy, classical studies, history, or literary criticism, this work will make it necessary to reconceptualize how we understand this great Athenian poet and force us to recognize the political ramifications and underpinnings of his uproarious comedies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aPhilosophy : Ancient Greek Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aAmbler, Wayne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaldwin, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBonnette, Amy L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurns, Timothy W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeLuca, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrost, Bryan-Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrost, Bryan-Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHabib, Khalil M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLombardini, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLudwig, Paul W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMhire, Jeremy 